19#include <string>
20#include <map>
21#include <memory>
22#include <list>
23
24namespace ZXing {
25
26class ByteArray;
27class CustomData;
28
29/**
30* @author Sean Owen
31*/
32class ResultMetadata
33{
34public:
35
36 /**
37 * Represents some type of metadata about the result of the decoding that the decoder
38 * wishes to communicate back to the caller.
39 */
40 enum Key {
41
42 /**
43 * Unspecified, application-specific metadata. Maps to an unspecified {@link CustomData}.
44 */
45 OTHER,
46
47 /**
48 * Denotes the likely approximate orientation of the barcode in the image. This value
49 * is given as degrees rotated clockwise from the normal, upright orientation.
50 * For example a 1D barcode which was found by reading top-to-bottom would be
51 * said to have orientation "90". This key maps to an {@link Integer} whose
52 * value is in the range [0,360).
53 */
54 ORIENTATION,
55
56 /**
57 * <p>2D barcode formats typically encode text, but allow for a sort of 'byte mode'
58 * which is sometimes used to encode binary data. While {@link Result} makes available
59 * the complete raw bytes in the barcode for these formats, it does not offer the bytes
60 * from the byte segments alone.</p>
61 *
62 * <p>This maps to a {@link java.util.List} of byte arrays corresponding to the
63 * raw bytes in the byte segments in the barcode, in order.</p>
64 */
65 BYTE_SEGMENTS,
66
67 /**
68 * Error correction level used, if applicable. The value type depends on the
69 * format, but is typically a String.
70 */
71 ERROR_CORRECTION_LEVEL,
72
73 /**
74 * For some periodicals, indicates the issue number as an {@link Integer}.
75 */
76 ISSUE_NUMBER,
77
78 /**
79 * For some products, indicates the suggested retail price in the barcode as a
80 * formatted {@link String}.
81 */
82 SUGGESTED_PRICE,
83
84 /**
85 * For some products, the possible country of manufacture as a {@link String} denoting the
86 * ISO country code. Some map to multiple possible countries, like "US/CA".
87 */
88 POSSIBLE_COUNTRY,
89
90 /**
91 * For some products, the extension text
92 */
93 UPC_EAN_EXTENSION,
94
95 /**
96 * PDF417-specific metadata
97 */
98 PDF417_EXTRA_METADATA,
99
100 /**
101 * If the code format supports structured append and the current scanned code is part of one then the
102 * sequence number is given with it.
103 */
104 STRUCTURED_APPEND_SEQUENCE,
105
106 /**
107 * If the code format supports structured append and the current scanned code is part of one then the
108 * total code count is given with it.
109 */
110 STRUCTURED_APPEND_CODE_COUNT,
111
112 /**
113 * If the code format supports structured append and the current scanned code is part of one then the
114 * parity is given with it.
115 */
116 STRUCTURED_APPEND_PARITY,
117
118 };
119
120 int getInt(Key key, int fallbackValue = 0) const;
121 std::wstring getString(Key key) const;
122 std::list<ByteArray> getByteArrayList(Key key) const;
123 std::shared_ptr<CustomData> getCustomData(Key key) const;
124
125 void put(Key key, int value);
126 void put(Key key, const std::wstring& value);
127 void put(Key key, const std::list<ByteArray>& value);
128 void put(Key key, const std::shared_ptr<CustomData>& value);
129
130 void putAll(const ResultMetadata& other);
131
132private:
133 struct Value;
134 struct IntegerValue;
135 struct StringValue;
136 struct ByteArrayListValue;
137 struct CustomDataValue;
138
139 std::map<Key, std::shared_ptr<Value>> _contents;
140};
141
142} // ZXing
